WEBVTT

00:00:00.151 --> 00:00:01.271
Common reasoning trap.

00:00:02.172 --> 00:00:08.834
Assuming conflict avoidance preserves team harmony when it causally guarantees artificial harmony and stifled innovation.

00:00:09.915 --> 00:00:12.436
Team dysfunction is a predictable causal chain.

00:00:13.276 --> 00:00:16.777
The absence of trust mathematically guarantees the fear of conflict.

00:00:17.638 --> 00:00:22.239
Without trust, your team will not engage in the productive debate required for innovation.

00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:23.900
Perform a critique.

00:00:24.830 --> 00:00:32.066
evaluate a hypothetical team that consistently fails to commit to strategic decisions, resulting in ambiguity and hesitation.

00:00:33.048 --> 00:00:35.232
Trace this failure back through the causal chain.

00:00:36.174 --> 00:00:41.987
The lack of commitment is a direct symptom of the fear of conflict, which itself is rooted in an absence of trust.
